<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-01T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Conference/165b:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-01T16:00:00-05:00">November 1, 1937—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>434. Press reports Eden stated in Parliament today “The United States
                                took the initiative in convoking Nine Power Conference, etc.” <pb facs="0142" n="134" xml:id="pg_134"/> and “I feel I ought to
                                make it quite plain that the initiative for holding the Conference
                                in Brussels never came from us at all, but from the United
                                States.”</p>
                            <p>Please cable urgently text of what Eden actually said pertinent to
                                these statements.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>